    <name>Slight Side from Whahouse Bridge </name>
    <bounds minlat="54.3972706" minlon="-3.2330129" maxlat="54.4353200" maxlon="-3.2071437" />
  </metadata>
  <rte>
    <name>Slight Side from Whahouse Bridge </name>
    <desc>Slight Side (2,499 feet) is an outlying peak approximately a mile to the south of Scafell, the second highest peak in England. It's profile is that of a distinctive peak when seen from the Eskdale direction though it's the southernmost outpost of the Scafell massif.  </desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1932-description</url>
